Weather App Home - Pencil Design Suggestions
Canvas: mobile, 390 x 844
Goal: make Home feel visually consistent with Map bottom sheet.
Style source: dark map surface, blurred glass panels, 20-32px radii, thin blue-gray borders,
soft cyan accent icons, compact data cards, dense but breathable weather information.

Shared visual tokens
- Background: #071327 base with subtle vertical depth toward #0D1E30.
- Primary glass: #0D1E30 at 72% opacity, blur 20, border #7FA5C8 at 20%.
- Secondary glass: #13263A at 20% opacity, border #7FA5C8 at 20%.
- Accent: #7CC4FF for icons, small dividers, selected states.
- Primary text: #FFFFFF. Secondary text: #C4D5E4. Muted text: #9FB4C8.
- Main radius: 28-32 on hero/sheet containers, 16-20 on metric cards.
- Icons: Lucide line icons, 16-24px, circular pale-blue icon wells for primary conditions.
- Spacing: 20px screen gutters, 12px grid gaps, 16-20px section padding.

Data priority for all designs
- Always visible: city, condition, current temperature, feels like.
- Primary insights: precipitation chance, wind speed, humidity.
- Secondary insights: UV index, sunrise, sunset, pressure if available later.
- Forecasts: compact hourly chips and 5-7 day rows.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESIGN 1 - "Sheet Home"
Best when you want Home to feel like the Map bottom sheet expanded into a full screen.

Pencil sketch

  .------------------------------------------------.
  |  Sarajevo                         [ search ]   |
  |  Mostly sunny today                            |
  |                                                |
  |      .----------------------------------.      |
  |      |   (sun icon)       23 C          |      |
  |      |   Feels like 24 C                |      |
  |      |   Light breeze, low rain risk    |      |
  |      '----------------------------------'      |
  |                                                |
  |  .---------------- glass sheet ---------------.|
  |  |  _                                          ||
  |  |  Key conditions                             ||
  |  |                                            ||
  |  |  .--------------.  .--------------.        ||
  |  |  | precipitation|  | wind         |        ||
  |  |  | 10%          |  | 18.0 km/h    |        ||
  |  |  '--------------'  '--------------'        ||
  |  |  .--------------.  .--------------.        ||
  |  |  | humidity     |  | UV index     |        ||
  |  |  | 56%          |  | 5.2          |        ||
  |  |  '--------------'  '--------------'        ||
  |  |                                            ||
  |  |  Next hours                                ||
  |  |  [13:00 sun 22] [16:00 cloud 21] [...]     ||
  |  |                                            ||
  |  |  7-day forecast                            ||
  |  |  Today   sun      24 C / 15 C              ||
  |  |  Tue     cloud    21 C / 13 C              ||
  |  '--------------------------------------------'|
  |                                                |
  |  Home        Map        Alerts      Settings   |
  '------------------------------------------------'

Layout notes
- Top area is not a card. Keep it as quiet page chrome over dark background.
- Current weather summary uses a floating hero pill, matching the sheet header row:
  circular icon well left, city summary center, large temp right.
- Large primary glass sheet starts around y=210, radius 32, same as map bottom sheet.
- The first grid should be 2 x 2 and include precipitation, wind, humidity, UV.
- Hourly chips should reuse the bottom sheet mini-hour cards: 70px wide, #13263A 20%.
- Daily forecast rows should look like bottom sheet rows, not standalone heavy cards.

Implementation direction
- Replace the current separated header + stats + lists with one HomeWeatherSheet widget.
- Reuse or extract private bottom sheet card styles into shared weather glass components.
- Keep scrolling inside the page, not a draggable sheet on Home.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESIGN 2 - "Insight Deck"
Best when you want the Home screen to emphasize readable metrics first, with forecasts below.

Pencil sketch

  .------------------------------------------------.
  |  Sarajevo                                      |
  |  Updated 13:04                    (sun icon)   |
  |                                                |
  |  23 C                                          |
  |  Mostly sunny                                  |
  |                                                |
  |  .--------------------------------------------.|
  |  |  Today's highlights                         ||
  |  |                                            ||
  |  |  .-----------. .-----------. .-----------.  ||
  |  |  | rain      | | wind      | | humidity  |  ||
  |  |  | 10%       | | 18 km/h   | | 56%       |  ||
  |  |  '-----------' '-----------' '-----------'  ||
  |  |                                            ||
  |  |  .--------------------. .----------------.  ||
  |  |  | sunrise 06:15      | | sunset 19:45   |  ||
  |  |  '--------------------' '----------------'  ||
  |  '--------------------------------------------'|
  |                                                |
  |  .--------------------------------------------.|
  |  |  Hourly                                    ||
  |  |  [now 23] [14 24] [15 24] [16 21] [17 20] ||
  |  '--------------------------------------------'|
  |                                                |
  |  .--------------------------------------------.|
  |  |  Forecast                                  ||
  |  |  Today   sun      24 C      15 C           ||
  |  |  Tue     cloud    21 C      13 C           ||
  |  |  Wed     rain     18 C      11 C           ||
  |  '--------------------------------------------'|
  |                                                |
  |  Home        Map        Alerts      Settings   |
  '------------------------------------------------'

Layout notes
- Hero weather remains unframed and prominent, preventing the screen from becoming a stack of cards.
- "Today's highlights" is the main sheet-like glass panel.
- Use three compact top metrics in a horizontal row for precipitation, wind, humidity.
- Sunrise/sunset use wider half-width pills to avoid cramped labels.
- Forecast modules below should be glass bands, not floating cards nested in cards.

Implementation direction
- Add a WeatherHighlights widget with adaptive grid:
  row 1: three equal metrics on width >= 360; 2-column fallback below.
  row 2: two half-width time metrics.
- HourlyForecastList and DailyForecastList should adopt the same glass panel surface.
- This option changes the least navigation structure and reads well on smaller phones.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESIGN 3 - "Compact Control Panel"
Best when you want a denser operational dashboard, closer to the map overlay controls.

Pencil sketch

  .------------------------------------------------.
  |  .--------------------------------------------.|
  |  | Sarajevo                         [locate]  ||
  |  | Mostly sunny today                         ||
  |  |                                            ||
  |  |  23 C                 feels 24 C           ||
  |  |  (sun icon)           low rain risk        ||
  |  '--------------------------------------------'|
  |                                                |
  |  [ Overview ] [ Wind ] [ Rain ] [ Sun ]        |
  |                                                |
  |  .--------------------------------------------.|
  |  | Overview metrics                            ||
  |  |                                            ||
  |  |  precipitation  10%       humidity  56%    ||
  |  |  wind           18 km/h   UV        5.2    ||
  |  |  sunrise        06:15     sunset    19:45  ||
  |  '--------------------------------------------'|
  |                                                |
  |  .--------------------------------------------.|
  |  | Temperature trend                           ||
  |  |      24       24                            ||
  |  |  23     23          21      20              ||
  |  |  now   14   15   16   17   18              ||
  |  '--------------------------------------------'|
  |                                                |
  |  .--------------------------------------------.|
  |  | Daily outlook                               ||
  |  | Today  sun       24 / 15                    ||
  |  | Tue    cloud     21 / 13                    ||
  |  '--------------------------------------------'|
  |                                                |
  |  Home        Map        Alerts      Settings   |
  '------------------------------------------------'

Layout notes
- Top summary is a single glass panel, similar to a map floating search/control surface.
- Segmented chips mirror map layer chips, but filter the metric panel rather than map layers.
- Default tab is Overview; Wind/Rain/Sun can later show focused detail without changing layout.
- Metric area is a dense two-column list, which is better for many readings than small cards.
- Trend panel can start as hourly chips and evolve into a simple line chart later.

Implementation direction
- Build a HomeMetricTabs widget using the same chip styling as MapLayerChips.
- Use a MetricRowsPanel for precipitation, wind, humidity, UV, sunrise, sunset.
- Keep cards full-width bands with no nested card hierarchy.
- This option is the most scalable if you plan to add pressure, visibility, air quality,
  dew point, or detailed wind direction later.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Recommended direction
Use Design 1 if the priority is visual consistency with the map bottom sheet.
Use Design 2 if the priority is readability and a balanced home dashboard.
Use Design 3 if the priority is future extensibility and denser weather tooling.

My recommended implementation path:
1. Start with Design 1 as the visual target.
2. Extract shared glass styles from map bottom sheet into a reusable widget or theme helper.
3. Add precipitation, wind, humidity, UV, sunrise, and sunset to the home sheet.
4. Restyle hourly and daily forecast sections to use the same surface, spacing, and typography.
